// Grammar used by the error-recovery oracle tests (issue #43).
//
// A small left-recursive sum grammar: every token (`NUMBER`, `+`) is globally
// lexable, so a grammatically-misplaced token (e.g. a stray `+` where a NUMBER
// is expected) surfaces as a token-level parse error the recovery loop can delete
// — exactly the panic-mode single-token-deletion path, and exactly what Python
// Lark's `on_error=lambda e: True` does.
start: sum
?sum: product
    | sum "+" product   -> add
?product: NUMBER
NUMBER: /[0-9]+/
%ignore " "
